3 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-9-102a of Title 10A, unless
5 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 A. The Oklahoma Commission on Children and Youth shall provide
7 for the creation and maintenance of a secure database to be utilized
8 by freestanding multidisciplinary child abuse teams during case
9 review.
10 B. The database shall collect case information and shall
11 maintain strict security of all information. The database and its
12 use shall be subject to the confidential records requirements
13 established pursuant to Sections 1-6-102 and 1-6-107 of this title
14 and penalties for violations established pursuant to Section 1-6-107
15 of this title.
16 C. The purpose of the database shall include, but not be
17 limited to:
18 1. Facilitating case management;
19 2. Providing for appropriate and uniform collection and
20 reporting of case information by all freestanding multidisciplinary
21 child abuse teams;
22 3. Enabling Commission staff to conduct programmatic
23 evaluations; and
24
Req. No. 12957 Page 9

1 4. Identifying trends to make recommendations for improving the
2 children and youth service system.
3 D. The Commission shall promulgate rules necessary to implement
4 the provisions of this section.
5 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
